Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> For roasted asparagus: Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Swap in asparagus for potatoes; roast until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}. (Save potatoes for another use.)

Meanwhile, quarter @lemon{1}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Pick @dill{1/4%ounce} fronds from stems; finely chop fronds.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @miso sauce concentrate{1%unit}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use ½ tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Place chickpeas in a #medium bowl{} and mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until about half the chickpeas are smooth (leave some larger chickpeas pieces for texture-packed bites!).

Stir in scallions, half the mayonnaise mixture, as much dill as you like, and lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add @sourdough bread{4%slice}; toast until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (Work in batches if necessary, adding more butter for each batch.)

In a second medium bowl (large bowl for 4 servings), toss @spinach{2.5%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, salt, and pepper.

Spread half the sourdough slices with remaining mayonnaise mixture.

Fill with chickpea salad and as much spinach as you like. Close sandwiches and halve on a diagonal.

Divide sandwiches, potato wedges, and any remaining spinach between plates. Serve.